    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I want to update this question with a screenshot of a recent Android Studio. It took a bit of poking around to find where to install new system images.</p>\n\n<p>You get to the SDK Manager through one of two paths.\nOption 1. Tools > Android > SDK Manager\nOption 2. Android Studio > Preferences > Appearance &amp; Behavior > System Settings > Android SDK (This is for Mac; adapt for others.)</p>\n\n<p>In the pane \"SDK Platforms,\" check the \"Show Packages\" box to see the system images.</p>\n\n<p>Select the ones you want, click \"Apply\" and voilà! </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/uun4b.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/uun4b.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  } ],
